    <name>
				<text>W4 Q03 Lagrange multiplier</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Find the maximum and minimum values of \[f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\] subject to \[ {@C@}.\] Write the Lagrange function in the form \(f({@v1@},{@v2@}) - \lambda g({@v1@},{@v2@})\).</p>
<p><b>(a)</b> For which values of \({@v1@}\) do critical points of \( f- \lambda g\) occur? </p><p>\( x = \) [[input:ansx]] [[validation:ansx]]</p>
<p><b>(b)</b> The maximum/minimum of \(f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\) subject to \( {@C@}\) is<br></p><p>\(\mbox{max} = \) [[input:ansmax]] [[validation:ansmax]]</p><p>\(\mbox{min} = \) [[input:ansmin]] [[validation:ansmin]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>To find the maximum and minimum values of 
\[f({@v1@},{@v2@})={@f@}\] 
subject to \( {@C@}\) we use the method of Lagrange multipliers.</p>
<p>In general we have the function \(f({@v1@},{@v2@})\) and the constraint \(g({@v1@},{@v2@}) = {@lhs(C)-rhs(C)@}=0\).</p>
<p>We write \[ \phi({@v1@},{@v2@},\lambda) = f({@v1@},{@v2@})+\lambda\, g({@v1@},{@v2@}) = {@f@}+ \lambda ({@(lhs(C)-rhs(C))@})^{**}\]
and then solve
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial{@v1@}} = {@DP1@}=0\]
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial{@v2@}} = {@DP2@}=0\]
\[ \frac{\partial \phi}{\partial {@l@}} = {@DPl@}=0\]
This gives us three equations in three unknowns, \( {@v1@},{@v2@},{@l@}\), which can be solved to get:
\[ {@ssol@}.\]
Evaluating \(f\) at each of these points gives respective values as \( \left[{@tamax@}, {@tamin@} \right] \).&nbsp;</p><p>Hence the minimum value is {@tamin@} and the maximum value is {@tamax@}.</p><p>\( ** \) Because we are using the variable \(l\) as part of the Maxima code we replace \( \lambda \) with \(l.\)</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
